 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Protection from Evil
@70023 = ~Wand of Protection from Evil~
@70024 = ~When activated, the wand creates a magical barrier around the recipient at a distance of one foot. The barrier has three effects: First, it bestows a +2 bonus to the recipient's Armor Class and Saving Throws against attacks from evil-aligned opponents; second, it prevents summoned fiends from attacking the recipient; third, it makes the recipient immune to charm-based spells or effects (e.g. Charm Person, Charm Person or Mammal, Domination, and so on).

STATISTICS:
(Abjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Protection from Evil
  – +2 AC bonus against attacks from Evil creatures
  – +2 Saving Throw bonus against attacks from Evil creatures
  – Protected from summoned demons
  – Immune to Charm effects
  Range: Touch
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 1 creature

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Shocking Grasp
@70027 = ~Wand of Shocking Grasp~
@70028 = ~When activated, the wand electrically charges the wielder's hands; this charge will deal 1d8+%magnitude% points of electrical damage to a targeted creature. The spell always hits unless the wielder is disrupted.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Shocking Grasp
  – Creates an electric charge damaging target
  Damage: 1d8+%magnitude% points of electrical damage
  Range: Touch
  Duration: Instant
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Sleep
@70029 = ~Wand of Sleep~
@70030 = ~This wand will emit a gold beam of energy at its targets, affecting 2d4 Hit Dice of creatures within a 9-ft. radius. Monsters with 5 or more Hit Dice are unaffected. Though it's not the stuff of which legends are made, attacks against magically sleeping opponents never miss—although they will awaken after the first hit.

STATISTICS:
(Enchantment/Charm)

Charge abilities:
– Sleep
  – Causes creatures in affected area to fall asleep
  Range: Sight
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 9-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Chill Touch
@60031 = ~Wand of Chill Touch~
@60032 = ~When activated, a blue glow encompasses the wielder's hand, and <PRO_HESHE> uses this energy to attack the life force of of any creature upon which the wielder makes a successful melee attack. The touched creature must make a Save vs. Wand or suffer 1d4 points of cold damage and receive a -1 THAC0 penalty for 1 turn after being struck.

An undead creature suffers no damage or to-hit penalty from Chill Touch, but will be affected by panic for 2 turns unless it successfully makes a Save vs. Spell.

STATISTICS:
(Necromancy)

Charge abilities:
– Chill Touch
  – Living:
    – Cold energy attack
    – -1 penalty to THAC0 to target for 1 turn
  – Undead:
    – Suffer panic for 2 turns
  Damage:
    – 1d4 cold damage
  Range: Touch
  Duration: 1 turn
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~
